ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Install Nginx

Installed Nginx using the package manager and verified the service status.
Copy code
Bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nginx
Checked service status:
Copy code
Bash
sudo systemctl status nginx
âœ” Nginx service started successfully.

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Create Website Directory

Created a custom directory to host the website.
Copy code
Bash
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/secure-site
Set ownership and permissions:
Copy code
Bash
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /var/www/secure-site
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/secure-site

ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Create Web Page

Created a simple HTML page.
Copy code
Bash
nano /var/www/secure-site/index.html
Sample content:

Html
<h1>Welcome to my Nginx Web Server</h1>
<p>Project by Ishant Parashar</p>

ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Configure Nginx Server Block

Created a custom server block configuration.
Copy code
Bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/secure-site
Configured Nginx to serve content from /var/www/secure-site.
Enabled the site:

Bash
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/secure-site /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
Tested configuration:
Copy code
Bash
sudo nginx -t
Restarted Nginx:
Copy code
Bash
sudo systemctl restart nginx

